## PR Title
DOC: Fix linkcode_resolve for inherited properties

## PR Body
The @inherit_names decorator creates property wrappers at runtime that delegate to the underlying Array class. These wrappers confuse Sphinx's introspection, causing all inherited properties to link to extension.py instead of their actual implementations. We detect this pattern and redirect to the true source location.\n\nFixes #58350\n\n- [x] closes #58350\n- [ ] Tests added and passed (not applicable - documentation infrastructure fix)\n- [x] All code checks passed\n- [ ] Added type annotations (not applicable - no new functions)\n- [ ] Added an entry in the latest whatsnew file (not needed - documentation infrastructure)\n\n## Description\nFixed the [source] button links for inherited properties (e.g., DatetimeIndex.quarter). Similar issues were found for other decorators (year, month, time, microsecond, etc.), which were incorrectly pointing to extension.py instead of their actual implementations in the Array classes.

